managePosition.t.sol
├── when call is reentrant
│  └── it should revert
└── when call is not reentrant
   ├── when the module is suspended
   │  └── it should revert with Suspended
   └── when the module is not suspended
      ├── when the module is paused
      │  └── it should revert with Paused
      └── when the module is not paused
         ├── when caller is not a registered operator
         │  └── it should revert with UnauthorizedCaller
         └── when caller is a registered operator
            ├── when the first instruction position ID is null
            │  └── it should revert with ZeroPositionId
            └── when the first instruction position ID is non null
               ├── when the first instruction is not of type management
               │  └── it should revert with InvalidInstructionType
               └── when the first instruction is of type management
                  ├── given the first instruction proof is not valid against the merkle root set in the module
                  │  └── it should revert with InvalidInstructionProof
                  └── given the first instruction proof is valid against the merkle root set in the module
                     ├── given lockdown mode is off
                     │  ├── when a second instruction is provided
                     │  │  ├── when the 2 instructions position IDs or isDebt flags do not match
                     │  │  │  └── it should revert with InstructionsMismatch
                     │  │  └── when the 2 instructions position IDs and isDebt flags match
                     │  │     ├── given the second instruction proof is not valid against the merkle root set in the module
                     │  │     │  └── it should revert with InvalidInstructionProof
                     │  │     └── given the second instruction proof is valid against the merkle root set in the module
                     │  │        ├── given the second instruction execution fails
                     │  │        │  └── it should revert
                     │  │        └── given the second instruction execution succeeds
                     │  │           ├── given the second instruction does not output a valid state
                     │  │           │  └── it should revert with InvalidAccounting
                     │  │           └── given the second instruction outputs a valid state
                     │  │              ├── when an instruction's affected tokens list contains tokens for which price data is not registered
                     │  │              │  └── it should revert with PriceFeedRouteNotRegistered
                     │  │              └── when instructions affected tokens list only contains tokens with registered price data
                     │  │                 ├── given the first instruction execution fails
                     │  │                 │  └── it should revert
                     │  │                 └── given the first instruction execution succeeds
                     │  │                    └── it should emit a PositionManaged event, including new position value
                     │  └── when no second instruction is provided
                     │     ├── given the first instruction execution fails
                     │     │  └── it should revert
                     │     └── given the first instruction execution succeeds
                     │        └── it should emit a PositionManaged event, including 0 as position value
                     └── given lockdown mode is on
                        ├── when no second instruction is provided
                        │  └── it should revert with AccountingMandatory
                        └── when a second instruction is provided
                           ├── given the module's safe globally spends tokens and the position value moves in wrong direction
                           │  └── it should revert with InvalidPositionChangeDirection
                           └── given the module's safe globally receives tokens or the position moves in expected direction
                              ├── given the position value increased
                              │     ├── given the relative value loss in the caliber is greater than maxPositionIncreaseLossBps
                              │     │  └── it should revert with MaxValueLossExceeded
                              │     └── given the relative value loss in the caliber is not greater than maxPositionIncreaseLossBps
                              │        ├── it should emit a PositionManaged event, including new position value
                              │        └── it should return the resulting new value and the value change resulting from management
                              └── given the position value did not increase
                                 ├── given the relative value loss in the caliber is greater than maxPositionDecreaseLossBps
                                 │  └── it should revert with MaxValueLossExceeded
                                 └── given the relative value loss in the caliber is not greater than maxPositionDecreaseLossBps
                                    ├── it should emit a PositionManaged event, including new position value
                                    └── it should return the resulting new value and the value change resulting from management
